<exercise xml:id="exercise-symb-lang-taut-contra-1">
	<!-- \label{EXERCISE::symb.lang::taut.contra.1} -->
	<introduction><p> Suppose <m>A,E,U</m> are logical statements such that <m>U</m> is a tautology and <m>E</m> is a contradiction. </p></introduction>
	<task><p> Show that <m>A \lgcor U</m> is always a tautology. </p></task>
	<task><p> Show that <m>A \lgcand E</m> is always a contradiction. </p></task>
</exercise>

<exercise><p>
	Suppose that <m>A</m>, <m>B</m>, and <m>C</m> are logical statements such that <m>A \lgcimplies B</m> and <m>B \lgcimplies C</m>.
	Must <m>A \lgcimplies C</m>?
</p></exercise>

</exercises>
